laboratory_examinations.findings: 1 cm cystic lesion in the uncinate process may represent an intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm. Appendix is fluid-filled, enlarged measuring maximally 13 mm with hyperemic mucosa and wall edema. No bowel obstruction. No free fluid or pneumoperitoneum, no abscess seen.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION.
